<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<title>Simple Selector</title>
<style> /* Element selector */
p {
color: blue;
}
/* ID Selector */
#main {
color : red;
}
/* Class Selector */
.note {
color: green;
}
/* Group Selector */
h1, h2 {
text-align: center;
}
/* Universal Selector */
* {
font-family: Arial;
}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<h1 id = "main">CSS Selectors</h1>
<h2>INTRODUCTION</h2>
<p>SELECTOR FORMS.</p>
<p Class="note">A CSS selector is used to select HTML elements so that we can apply styles(color, size, layout, etc.) to them.</p>
</body>
</html>
